ct\":\"Actual sequence number received\",\"seqNumExp\":\"Expected sequence number based upon caller\"}}],\"SeqNumGap(uint40,uint40,address)\":[{\"details\":\"Occurs when seq num `rcvd` > `expect`, possible causes: error from network/provider/client/reorg     - Invariant: `seqNum` must increment monotonically for a write call, see table above\",\"params\":{\"caller\":\"Caller's address\",\"seqNumAct\":\"Received sequence number\",\"seqNumExp\":\"Expected sequence number\"}}]},\"events\":{\"ReqAck(bytes16,address,uint40,(bytes16,uint16,uint16,uint16,uint40,uint40),bool)\":{\"details\":\"A Request Acknowledgement Event occurs at the end of each request (if no revert) and bridges the gaps between data sources, clients, lossy/unreliable protocols/providers/neworks, and the on-chain call outcome - Captures 3 categories of data for off-chain calls:     - Key inputs (indexed params) allow a tx search via either:         - PK1: reqId: Allows a tx search on a single field such as to fill a gap on replay         - PK2: (caller,seqNum): Allows a tx search to audit a sequence for a caller     - Context: `replay` and `callRes.blockNum` provide context on when/where this happened     - Output: `callRes` provides fields (rc, lrc, count) for either a simple result or summary         - Additional results can be found in the tx receipt logs from prior events in the same tx\",\"params\":{\"callRes\":\"See `CallRes`; `reqId` and `ReqAck` are separate params for indexes\",\"caller\":\"Account initiating the tx\",\"replay\":\"false for an original event, true when `reqId` was already processed\",\"reqId\":\"From CallRes: Request ID, allows for gap-fill on replay\",\"seqNum\":\"From CallRes: Caller's sequence number incremented monotonically\"}}},\"kind\":\"dev\",\"methods\":{},\"version\":1},\"userdoc\":{\"kind\":\"user\",\"methods\":{},\"version\":1}},\"settings\":{\"compilationTarget\":{\"contract/v1_0/IContractUser.sol\":\"IContractUser\"},\"evmVersion\":\"prague\",\"libraries\":{},\"m